    <node id="RT-DETR">
      <data key="entity_id">RT-DETR</data>
      <data key="entity_type">concept</data>
      <data key="description">RT-DETR is a real-time end-to-end object detector proposed in the text, designed to improve speed and accuracy in object detection.&lt;SEP&gt;RT-DETR is a proposed Transformer-based solution for real-time object detection, introduced in the research paper.&lt;SEP&gt;RT-DETR is the proposed object detection model that achieves state-of-the-art performance according to Figure 1.&lt;SEP&gt;RT-DETR is a real-time end-to-end object detection model designed to improve accuracy and performance.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-f8619065465d075892731f2a8b8555e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-faafaa17742ca7c753025687b423a9a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef8c7ff567b0412204b7096eef345f02</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773520736</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="Transformer Encoder">
      <data key="entity_id">Transformer Encoder</data>
      <data key="entity_type">method</data>
      <data key="description">Transformer encoder is a component of the DETR model that processes features but is replaced in RT-DETR with a hybrid encoder.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-f8619065465d075892731f2a8b8555e6</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773520656</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="DETR">
      <data key="entity_id">DETR</data>
      <data key="entity_type">concept</data>
      <data key="description">DETR is an end-to-end object detection model based on the Transformer architecture, which RT-DETR improves upon.&lt;SEP&gt;DETR is an object detection model that uses a transformer architecture for end-to-end detection.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-f8619065465d075892731f2a8b8555e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef8c7ff567b0412204b7096eef345f02</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773520736</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="YOLO Detectors">
      <data key="entity_id">YOLO Detectors</data>
      <data key="entity_type">concept</data>
      <data key="description">YOLO detectors are a family of one-stage real-time object detection models that RT-DETR outperforms in both speed and accuracy.&lt;SEP&gt;YOLO detectors are a class of object detection models that have limitations in terms of Non-Maximum Suppression (NMS).</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-f8619065465d075892731f2a8b8555e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-faafaa17742ca7c753025687b423a9a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef8c7ff567b0412204b7096eef345f02</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773520736</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="COCO Val2017">
      <data key="entity_id">COCO Val2017</data>
      <data key="entity_type">data</data>
      <data key="description">COCO Val2017 is a benchmark dataset used for evaluating object detection models.&lt;SEP&gt;COCO Val2017 is a dataset used to evaluate the performance of RT-DETR, measuring its AP (Average Precision).</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-f8619065465d075892731f2a8b8555e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-480c8136267783fba29416e2dcbc0522</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773520656</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="NMS">
      <data key="entity_id">NMS</data>
      <data key="entity_type">concept</data>
      <data key="description">NMS (Non-Maximum Suppression) is a post-processing technique used in object detection to remove overlapping bounding boxes.&lt;SEP&gt;NMS is a post-processing algorithm used in object detection to eliminate overlapping output boxes by applying confidence and IoU thresholds.&lt;SEP&gt;NMS is a post-processing algorithm used in object detection to eliminate overlapping boxes, which RT-DETR eliminates.&lt;SEP&gt;NMS stands for Non-Maximum Suppression, a technique used in object detection to eliminate redundant detections.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-f8619065465d075892731f2a8b8555e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56050e109fbbcac2d20804a62750188c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-480c8136267783fba29416e2dcbc0522&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef8c7ff567b0412204b7096eef345f02</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773520739</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="AP">
      <data key="entity_id">AP</data>
      <data key="entity_type">data</data>
      <data key="description">AP stands for Average Precision, a metric used to evaluate the accuracy of object detection models.&lt;SEP&gt;AP refers to Average Precision, a metric used to evaluate the accuracy of object detection models like RT-DETR.&lt;SEP&gt;AP stands for Average Precision, a metric used to evaluate the performance of object detection models.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-f8619065465d075892731f2a8b8555e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56050e109fbbcac2d20804a62750188c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef8c7ff567b0412204b7096eef345f02</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773520739</data>
