    <node id="RT-DETR Research Paper Page 1 (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">RT-DETR Research Paper Page 1 (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image is the first page of the academic paper introducing RT-DETR, a real-time end-to-end object detector. It features the title, author list, abstract, introduction, and Figure 1. Figure 1 is a critical performance comparison chart demonstrating that RT-DETR (red markers) outperforms existing YOLO series detectors (various colors) in both accuracy (COCO AP) and speed (latency) on a T4 GPU, validating the paper's central claim.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-faafaa17742ca7c753025687b423a9a9</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773520711</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RT-DETR Paper Page 2 Text Column (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">RT-DETR Paper Page 2 Text Column (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image contains the left-hand text column of page 2 from the research paper introducing RT-DETR. It bridges the introduction and related work sections, detailing the technical innovations of the RT-DETR architecture (hybrid encoder, query selection) and its superior performance over YOLO and DINO models. The text also initiates a literature review on real-time and end-to-end object detectors, providing essential context for the study's contribution to computer vision.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-ef8c7ff567b0412204b7096eef345f02</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773520711</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Page 3 of Research Paper on Object Detection Speed and NMS Analysis (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">Page 3 of Research Paper on Object Detection Speed and NMS Analysis (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image captures page 3 of a scientific paper analyzing the end-to-end speed of object detectors. It features a bar chart comparing box counts for YOLOv5 and YOLOv8 across different confidence thresholds, and a table detailing the impact of IoU and confidence thresholds on Average Precision (AP) and Non-Maximum Suppression (NMS) execution time. The accompanying text discusses the computational costs of NMS, query initialization in DETR models, and establishes a benchmarking protocol using the COCO dataset.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-28af5b45934b05fde5ec1892d56def9a</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773520711</data>
    </node>
